      "content": "It's never a good idea to adjust the dosage of medications on your own, including zolpidem. Both alcohol and medications like zolpidem can affect your body's ability to metabolize and process them safely, increasing the risk of side effects and potential health issues. It's crucial to follow your doctor's prescription exactly as directed. If you have concerns about your dosage or the interaction with alcohol, please speak with your doctor. They can provide safe, personalized advice and explore other solutions that don't involve compromising your health. Remember, there's always a safer and healthier way to address sleep issues.",
